GOLDEN ADAGE gave chase, rounded the turn about the four path and ran evenly in the lane. Z MYSTIQUE chased inside, raced in the four path on the turn then flattened in the lane. MISCHIEVIOUS BOY was bumped leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. COMO ESTAS stumbled leaving the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path and weakened in the lane. ROBBEDINTHEBAHAMAS gave chase outside and rounded the turn about the five path. RAMBUNCTIOUS RIDE broke inward and into Amende Charlie leaving the gate, raced well back and rounded the turn off the rail.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESPRESSO bore out into the opening turn but corrected course and took a slim lead approaching the half mile pole, dueled from that point but was met at the three eighths and contested even terms, rounded the far turn two deep, dueled clear mid-stretch and held on driving. CALYPSO JOHN rounded the first turn about the four path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced two deep on the far turn, dug in from the head of the lane and dueled through the final furlong for second. GREATANDGOOD raced off the pace in the three path the first turn, started a bid toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. JUST MURPHY settled off the rail on the first turn then stalked into the backstretch, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths, drifted leaving the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. ALDARIGHTTRICKS took the lead at the rail into the first turn and rated the early pace, was met toward the half mile pole and dueled at mostly even terms through the backstretch, contested the rail through the far turn but flattened stride nearing mid-stretch. JUST CALL ME AL had a brief early lead but was forced out into the opening turn, left the turn outside and gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and showed little more. MOON FALL showed little response through the backstretch. DON'T GET CAUGHTUP was not a factor. I SEE NOTHING saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. THEIRREGISTRDIMNOT stumbled and lost his rider at the break. A Stewards inquiry and subsequent claim of foul against the rider of Espresso for interference into the first turn, lodged by the rider of Just Call Me Al, resulted in the disqualification of the former to sixth place.

ENTRY.NAME: Just Call Me Al
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced out into 1st turn,chased 3/8,3p far turn,empty lane

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUMPIN JACK BRASS rated close off the rail on the first turn then stalked three wide into the backstretch, dueled at near even terms leaving the five sixteenths pole, took the nod midway on the far turn, raced clear toward mid-stretch and drew off the final sixteenth. LA MADDALENA stalked from the two and three paths, challenged nearing the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms between horses through the backstretch, raced close two deep on the far turn, relented nearing mid-stretch, though, held on for second. IHEARTRAINACOMN rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms from that point, contested the rail on the far turn then flattened in the stretch. DENALI D'ORO saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. FRENCHIES GOLD was bumped then pinched back at the start and saved ground racing well back early, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the seven path and could only improve her position. SPARKLEINYOUREYE stumbled to her nose and made contact with Frenchies Gold leaving the gate then saved ground, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths and showed little in the lane. JUST HAVE FAITH raced well off the pace in the three path the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. DEREKA'S BLUFF rounded the first turn in the four path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the five path on the far turn. PHILMARY CASTLE rated close to the early pace inside, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. PRINCESS HALO ducked out and made contact with Frenchies Gold leaving the gate, raced in the four path the first turn and showed little response.
